        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 3:54AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 353 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Freeport to Mount Morris to near Amboy.
Movement was northeast at 40 mph. A few personal weather stations
across Stephenson, Carroll, and Whiteside counties recorded 40 to 50
mph wind gusts with these storms.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Oregon, Pecatonica, Rockford Airport, Seward, Lindenwood, Lake
Summerset, Grand Detour, Ashton, Kings, Chana, Loves Park, Franklin
Grove, Cherry Valley, Hillcrest, South Beloit, Stillman Valley, New
Milford, Rockton, Byron, Leaf River, Mount Morris, Winnebago,
Shirland, Machesney Park, and Davis Junction.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
